  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6942.49 sitting just below the massive 6950 gamma wall (+19.4B), dealers are likely selling into this momentum as they hedge their long gamma positions, creating natural resistance. The PIN regime with spot well above the 6856 flip point means dealers will continue providing stabilizing flows - selling rallies into the 6950-7000 zone and buying any dips toward 6925-6900 support levels. Watch for rejection at 6950 given the wall break detection and enormous positive gamma concentration there, with 6925 as the next key support if momentum fades.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect selling pressure into 6950 with choppy action between 6925-6950.",
